  "prompt": "I failed all technical interviews at Facebook, Google, Microsoft, Amazon and Apple. Should I give up the big companies and try some small startups?",
  "response": "Here are some constructive suggestions:\n\n1. Don't give up, but do reflect:\n- Analyze why you're failing interviews\n- Get detailed feedback if possible\n- Identify specific skill/knowledge gaps\n\n2. Improve technical skills:\n- Practice data structures and algorithms\n- Do more LeetCode/HackerRank problems\n- Take online courses (algorithms, system design)\n- Study computer science fundamentals\n\n3. Prepare interview strategies:\n- Mock interviews with peers\n- Improve communication during technical interviews\n- Work on problem-solving approach\n- Practice whiteboarding/coding under pressure\n\n4. Consider alternative paths:\n- Mid-size tech companies\n- Startups (good suggestion)\n- Local companies with strong engineering teams\n- Contract/consulting roles\n\n5. Professional development:\n- Build strong GitHub portfolio\n- Contribute to open-source projects\n- Network with industry professionals\n- Consider additional certifications\n\n6. Realistic perspective:\n- These interviews are extremely competitive\n- Many talented engineers face multiple rejections\n- Persistence and continuous learning are key\n\nRemember: Rejection is part of the growth process. Keep improving and stay motivated.\n\nWould you like to discuss specific areas where you struggled in these interviews?",
